clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ak1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ak1" class="parent"><a name="1ak1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ak1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ak1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ak1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ABranco/">ABranco</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 03:52:12AM</span><span class="votes " >12 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ak1'] = ['11 points', '12 points', '13 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ak1')">[+] (9 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ak1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ak1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ABranco/">ABranco</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 03:52:12AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ak1'>12 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ak1'] = ['11 points', '12 points', '13 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ak1')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ak1" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p><em>I will repeat this point again until I get hoarse: a mistake is not something to be determined after the fact, but in the light of the information until that point. —Nicholas Nassim Taleb</em></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ak1"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ak1" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ak1')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ak1" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ak1')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ak1" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1hh/rationality_quotes_november_2009/1ak1?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ak1" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ak1')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ak1 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ak1" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ak1" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ak1" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1aki" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1aki" class="parent"><a name="1aki" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1aki" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1aki" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1aki" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 04:39:34AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1aki'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1aki')">[+] (8 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1aki" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1aki" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 04:39:34AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1aki'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1aki'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1aki')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1aki" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>This is something I actively remind myself whenever my intuition starts feeling vindication over lucky reprieves or mourning low probability misfortunes. <em>"It's ok, a six wasn't rolled anyway.</em> <strong>I made a mistake.</strong> It would have been better to trade the wood and build a settlement. <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/h8/tsuyoku_naritai_i_want_to_become_stronger/">I want to become stronger</a>.<em>"</em> (The hyperlink is included instead of the phrase. The inner dialog doesn't like wordiness!)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1aki"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1aki" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1aki')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1aki" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1aki')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1aki" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1hh/rationality_quotes_november_2009/1aki?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1aki" href="#1ak1" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1aki" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1aki')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1aki class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1aki" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1aki" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1aki" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1akn" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1akn" class="parent"><a name="1akn" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1akn" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1akn" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1akn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 05:12:13AM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1akn'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1akn')">[+] (7 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1akn" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1akn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 05:12:13AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1akn'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1akn'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1akn')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1akn" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I've played some Settlers of Catan myself, and it took me a while to realize what you were talking about. (If I understand correctly, you chose not to build a settlement next to a tile that produces resources when a 6 is rolled, and by chance, the settlement wouldn't have produced any resources this turn because a 6 wasn't rolled. Therefore, waiting a turn to build the settlement didn't actually hurt you, but it could have.) I see similar situations all the time when playing Magic.</p>

<p>Similarly, even if you do win the lottery, buying a negative expected value ticket was still a mistake.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1akn"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1akn" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1akn')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1akn" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1akn')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1akn" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1hh/rationality_quotes_november_2009/1akn?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1akn" href="#1aki" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1akn" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1akn')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1akn class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1akn" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1akn" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1akn" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1b0j" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1b0j" class="parent"><a name="1b0j" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1b0j" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1b0j" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1b0j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Blueberry/">Blueberry</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2009 08:35:06PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1b0j'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1b0j')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1b0j" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1b0j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Blueberry/">Blueberry</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2009 08:35:06PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1b0j'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1b0j'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1b0j')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1b0j" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>This also happens all the time in poker, especially when you see the flop and instinctively feel good (or bad) that you folded.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1b0j"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1b0j" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1b0j')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1b0j" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1b0j')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1b0j" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1hh/rationality_quotes_november_2009/1b0j?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1b0j" href="#1akn" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1b0j" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1b0j')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1b0j class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1b0j" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1al3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1al3" class="parent"><a name="1al3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1al3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1al3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1al3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 07:50:23AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1al3'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1al3')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1al3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1al3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 07:50:23AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1al3'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1al3'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1al3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1al3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>I've played some Settlers of Catan myself, and it took me a while to realize what you were talking about.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Well spotted!</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>If I understand correctly, you chose not to build a settlement next to a tile that produces resources when a 6 is rolled, and by chance, the settlement wouldn't have produced any resources this turn because a 6 wasn't rolled. Therefore, waiting a turn to build the settlement didn't actually hurt you, but it could have.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Yes, By forgetting I had a wood port I could have lost possible resources from a 6 or even more if a 7 came while the cards were still in my hand.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>I see similar situations all the time when playing Magic.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I see them rather less. I've played sufficiently few games that I mostly notice the mistakes when the cards drop and my Feral Hydra gets fried. RIP.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1al3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1al3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1al3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1al3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1al3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1al3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1hh/rationality_quotes_november_2009/1al3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1al3" href="#1akn" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1al3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1al3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1al3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1al3" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1al3" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1al3" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1al6" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1al6" class="parent"><a name="1al6" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1al6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1al6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1al6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 08:36:18AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1al6'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1al6')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1al6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1al6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 08:36:18AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1al6'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1al6'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1al6')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1al6" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I was mostly thinking about mulligans. If you kept a one land hand and go on to win because you drew three lands in a row, that doesn't mean keeping it was the right decision. Conversely, if you do mulligan your 7 card hand and then end up with completely unplayable 6 card and 5 card hands, that doesn't mean that you should have kept your original hand.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1al6"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1al6" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1al6')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1al6" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1al6')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1al6" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1hh/rationality_quotes_november_2009/1al6?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1al6" href="#1al3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1al6" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1al6')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1al6 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1al6" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1al6" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1al6" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1al8" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1al8" class="parent"><a name="1al8" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1al8" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1al8" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1al8" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 December 2009 09:09:19AM</span><span class="