s " id='score_t1_1adt'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1adt'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1adt')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1adt" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>...yeah, it's not a brilliant rationality quote, but there's a bit of a good point in it nonetheless: this is a case in which precommitment is necessary, because despite the fact that you would prefer not to be subject to the assault of an enemy, you don't want to establish that every threat will be profitable, however imaginary. Naive calculations neglect the effect of <em>your decision method</em> on the actions of others. (It's like in cryptography - your strategy has to work <em>even if</em> other people know the function.)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1adt"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1adt" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1adt')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1adt" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1adt')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1adt" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1hh/rationality_quotes_november_2009/1adt?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1adt" href="#1ada" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1adt" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1adt')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1adt class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1adt" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1adt" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1adt" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1adu" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1adu" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1adu" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1adu" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1adu" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1adu" class